<br>
However, once the raid exploit showed up, then yes I did see an influx of more and more problem people arrive...at all levels. It took time, but the raid exploit-no drop rule finally seeped out to the masses and some of the bad ones have come here to try and exploit it. Again, in no way can I say that these people have been transfers, because I don't know, but most have been lower than my level, so I'd think they were levelers not transfers. People say close the door to transfers...but this would stop a small amount of people who are coming over and being jerks about things. People who transfer over at the high end levels don't do it so they can come ruin other peoples fun, they are focused on the high end game. Who drops transfer money just so they can be an ass when you can level up and do it for free?<br>
<br>
As per F&amp;F and them not recruiting more of our people from FV. They have always recruited FV people but 90% of the FV players I know couldn't handle their raid requirements, pure and simple. Time is the most precious resource for these guilds...and I know people who have had a RL situation change and have to drop out, because they can't make the requirements. I know lots of people who would make fine members of any high end raiding guild, but they just don't have the time to do it. <br>
<br>
And as to the transfers not having the &quot;experience&quot; of FV to tame their wildest &quot;black ops characters who have gone off the reservation&quot; tendencies....look at the problem children we all know in the high end guilds. Every single one I know was raised  here. The nature overtook the nurture. An ass is an ass, no matter how they got here.<br>
