a hate to point it out, but this is a &quot;Roleplaying PREFERRED&quot; server. i personally don't feel that everyone who comes here should be required to roleplay, as long as they dont interfere too much with the RPers already here. we're both playing the same game, just for different reasons.... since when was that a bad thing?<br>
<br>
i support server transfers to FV because yes, it does help us get some high-level people who are great players and interested in coming to join us for whatever reason, because this is a pretty low population server so its hard to recruit at times, and the fact that many on the servers are roleplayers means that alot of them aren't going to meet our requirements, or WANT to meet them. thats totally fine by me. its hard to lower those requirements much more because they're already lower than most guilds at our level. server transfers also make it possible for someones friend to come join them on this server without having to start all over with leveling, whether that person is a roleplayer or a high end gamer. i think people are having a bit of a knee-jerk reaction in thinking that everyone who transfers here is or will be bad. transfers have been in for 2 months now almost, and i haven't heard of many problems happening in game because of it. <br>
<br>
i LOVE FV... i love raiding here, i love my guild, i love the atmosphere of the server. it's a great place to be. but i've come to realize, and i think maybe other people should, that roleplaying isn't always the reason that someone would come to this server. maybe it should have been, but that's not the way it turned out. i can't really see what's wrong about enjoying a different part of the game than someone else. i am pretty confident that anyone who does transfer to this server is probably not coming here to screw everyone over. they're either coming to join a friend, or coming to join a high end guild here. what is wrong about having those two seperate aspects? why can't both sides (roleplayers and high end gamers) learn to respect each others aspect of the game, seeing as how we both hardly ever come in contact with each other, and exist in harmony?<br>
<br>
and that would be my 2cp. alot of it has probably been said already in one way or another, but i needed to get my opinion out. i hope you all understand what i'm saying and maybe at least somewhat agree. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/cathead/fairy_bounce02.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
