<br>
God damn it its not even about that.  Read the friggen posts.  People need to STOP trying to make this rp vs uber or whatever happy horseshit makes their arguments more &quot;flashy.&quot;<br>
<br>
There's some people that want to make this Y vs X guild or server vs X guild.  Knock it the hell off thats not the point.  Start your own thread, dont drag this issue into it.<br>
<br>
FnF supports transfers.  They've admited it.  I'll argue till Im blue in the face against them, but at the end of the day... Ive got no beef with FnF OTHER then this issue.<br>
<br>
Ive never been treated poorly by a FnF member.  They've never pushed me in a puddle and taken my spawn.  I've never even really spoke with any of them.<br>
<br>
&quot;A-ha!&quot; They will say, &quot;The our transfers shouldnt be any concern of yours!&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, try reading what I said in my last post again.  I am full and well willing to admit that you are getting WONDERFUL people from other servers for your guild.<br>
<br>
However, FnF is NOT in charge of transfers for the rest of the server.  The high-quality recruites you are getting have the same green money as everyone else that will attempt to transfer here.  The quality of your people matters ZERO in this argument, because its all about potential problems and a desire to stop it before it gets out of hand.<br>
<br>
No one can predict the future.  The legion of poor players some of us fear may never arrive.  To many of us though, it is better to close the door then risk allowing them to enter through it.<br>
<br>
That is the point of this thread.  All the crap about FnF and people's little personal side issues dont belong here and only serve to detract from the real issue.  Just because their guild has a policy some people disagree with (and feel that said policy WILL affect them,) doesnt mean they are horriable aweful people that need to be shown the door, on EITHER side.<br>
<br>
FnF has as much right to be here as everyone else, and I hope people realize that is not at the root of this particular issue. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~Vabris Vy'Tok, of House Vy'Tok~<br>
